17 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
18 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
19 Article 5 – Calvert County
20 2–101.
21 (a) Five County Commissioners comprise the Board of County Commissioners of
22 Calvert County.
23 (b) (1) The annual salary of the president of the Board is[:
24 (I) $44,500 for calendar year 2018;
25 (II) $46,000 for calendar year 2019;
26 (III) $47,500 for calendar year 2020;
27 (IV) $49,000 for calendar year 2021; and
28 (V) $50,500 for calendar year 2022 and each subsequent calendar
29 year] $58,000.
30 (2) The annual salary of each of the associate members of the Board is[:
31 (I) $42,000 for calendar year 2018;

HOUSE BILL 1514 3
1 (II) $43,500 for calendar year 2019;
2 (III) $45,000 for calendar year 2020;
3 (IV) $46,500 for calendar year 2021; and
4 (V) $48,000 for calendar year 2022 and each subsequent calendar
5 year] $53,000.
6 (c) Each Commissioner may be reimbursed up to an annual total of $2,000, for
7 any reasonable costs incurred by the Commissioner in carrying out the functions of the
8 office.
9 (d) A Commissioner may participate in the Calvert County Employees
10 Retirement Savings Plan.
11 (E) AFTER 10 YEARS OF SERVICE AS A COMMISSIONER, REGARDLESS OF
12 AGE, A FORMER COMMISSIONER MAY RECEIVE BENEFITS UNDER THE COUNTY
13 RETIREE HEALTH BENEFITS PROGRAM.
14 Article – Criminal Procedure
15 15–405.
16 (a) This section applies only in Calvert County.
17 (b) [(1)] The State’s Attorney’s salary is equal to the salary of a circuit court
18 judge.
19 [(2) A salary increase shall take effect at the beginning of the elected term
20 of office and may not increase during the term of office.]
21 Article – Education
22 3–303.
23 (a) At its first meeting at the beginning of each calendar year, the county board
24 shall elect a president and a vice president from among its members.
25 (b) (1) The president of the county board is entitled to receive:
26 (I) $6,500 [annually] as compensation [and the] FOR CALENDAR
27 YEAR 2026; AND
28 (II) $8,500 AS COMPENSATION FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2027 AND
29 EACH SUBSEQUENT CALENDAR YEAR.

4 HOUSE BILL 1514
1 (2) THE other members OF THE COUNTY BOARD are entitled to receive:
2 (I) $5,500 [each annually] as compensation FOR CALENDAR YEAR
3 2026; AND
4 (II) $7,500 AS COMPENSATION FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2027 AND
5 EACH SUBSEQUENT CALENDAR YEAR.
6 [(2)] (3) An elected member is entitled to health insurance benefits
7 regularly provided to employees of the board of education under the same terms and
8 conditions extended to other employees of the board of education.
9 Article – Local Government
10 16–202.
11 (a) The annual salary of the County Treasurer of Calvert County is [$57,500]
12 $115,000.
13 (b) (1) The County Treasurer of Calvert County shall appoint one deputy
14 treasurer.
15 (2) The County Commissioners of Calvert County shall set the annual
16 salary of the deputy treasurer.
17 (c) (1) [An] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS
18 SUBSECTION:
19 (I) AN individual who serves as County Treasurer of Calvert County
20 for at least three terms shall receive an annual pension when the individual leaves office
21 of $150 for each year served[.
22 (2) The]; AND
23 (II) THE pension shall be paid at least once per month.
24 (2) BEGINNING WITH THE TERM OF OFFICE THAT BEGINS ON OR
25 AFTER NOVEMBER 4, 2026, AN INDIVIDUAL WHO SERVES AS COUNTY TREASURER
26 OF CALVERT COUNTY SHALL RECEIVE THE SAME PENSION BENEFITS AS COUNTY
27 EMPLOYEES.
28 (d) The County Commissioners of Calvert County shall:

HOUSE BILL 1514 5
1 (1) provide in its annual budget a pension of $150 per month to be paid to
2 the surviving spouse of any county treasurer who served as of October 1974; and
3 (2) pay the pension for the life of the surviving spouse.
4 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, in accordance with Article
5 III, § 35 of the Maryland Constitution, this Act may not be construed to extend or apply to
6 the salary or compensation of the County Commissioners of Calvert County, the president
7 and members of the Calvert County Board of Education, or the County Treasurer of Calvert
8 County while serving in a term of office beginning before the effective date of this Act, but
9 the provisions of this Act concerning the salary or compensation of the County
10 Commissioners of Calvert County, the president and members of the Calvert County Board
11 of Education, or the County Treasurer of Calvert County shall take effect at the beginning
12 of the next following term of office. This limitation does not apply to an individual appointed
13 or elected after the effective date of this Act to fill out an unexpired term.
14 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
15 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
